# Plan: Netflix-Style Video Collection Tab for Rugby Dashboard

## Context

The rugby coaching platform (`scripts/dashboard/rugby-web.mjs`, 2139 lines) already has a working drill library tab with filters, a practice planner, glossary, and coaches tabs. Videos are uploaded to Google Drive and stored as `gdrive_url` in drill note frontmatter. Currently, videos are hidden inside a per-card expand — you click a text card and an iframe appears inline. There is no way to browse videos visually.

The user wants a Netflix-style "Videos" tab: category rows with horizontal-scroll thumbnail strips, where clicking a card opens a fullscreen video modal. All infrastructure is already in place — the task is a UI-only addition to the existing dashboard file.

**One existing bug to fix**: the `gdrive_url` in `.cache/rugby/*-gdrive.json` uses the format `https://drive.google.com/open?id=<fileId>`, but the current embed regex (`/\/d\/([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)/`) only matches the `/file/d/<id>` path format. This means no videos currently embed. We'll fix this as part of the work.

---

## Critical File

- `scripts/dashboard/rugby-web.mjs` — sole file to modify (~2139 lines)

---

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Add `getDriveFileId(url)` helper
Insert a shared helper near the top of the client-side `<script>` block that extracts the Drive file ID from either URL format:
- `https://drive.google.com/open?id=<id>` → parse query param `id`
- `https://drive.google.com/file/d/<id>/...` → match path segment

```js
function getDriveFileId(url) {
  if (!url) return null;
  const m = url.match(/\/d\/([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)/);
  if (m) return m[1];
  try {
    return new URL(url).searchParams.get('id');
  } catch { return null; }
}
```

### 2. Fix the existing embed code
In `toggleCard()`, replace the current regex-only extraction with `getDriveFileId()`. Also fix the same pattern wherever it appears.

### 3. Add "Videos" tab button
In the `<div class="tab-bar">` HTML string, add:
```html
<button data-tab="videos" onclick="showTab('videos', this)">Videos</button>
```

### 4. Add `<div id="videosView">` section
Below `#drillsView`, add an empty `<div id="videosView" style="display:none;">` container.

### 5. Add Netflix CSS in `<style>` block
Add these rules to the existing `<style>` section:

```css
/* ── Videos tab ── */
.videos-view { padding: 20px; background: #0f1117; min-height: 100vh; color: #fff; }
.category-row { margin-bottom: 32px; }
.category-row h2 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 10px; }
.video-strip { display: flex; gap: 10px; overflow-x: auto; scroll-snap-type: x mandatory; padding-bottom: 6px; scrollbar-width: thin; }
.video-strip::-webkit-scrollbar { height: 4px; }
.video-strip::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #444; border-radius: 2px; }
.video-card { flex: 0 0 200px; scroll-snap-align: start; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; background: #1e2230; transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s; }
.video-card:hover { transform: scale(1.04); box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); z-index: 2; }
.video-thumb { width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; object-fit: cover; display: block; background: #2a2f40; }
.video-thumb-placeholder { width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; background: linear-gradient(135deg,#1e2230 0%,#2d3555 100%); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 1.8rem; }
.video-card-info { padding: 8px 10px 10px; }
.video-card-title { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: #eee; line-height: 1.3; margin-bottom: 4px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }
.video-card-meta { font-size: 0.68rem; color: #888; }
/* Modal */
.video-modal-backdrop { position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.94); z-index: 1000; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
.video-modal-inner { width: min(90vw, 1100px); }
.video-modal-iframe { width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; border: none; border-radius: 6px; background: #000; }
.video-modal-info { padding: 14px 4px 0; color: #ddd; }
.video-modal-info h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.video-modal-info p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #aaa; }
.video-modal-close { position: absolute; top: 18px; right: 22px; font-size: 1.6rem; background: none; border: none; color: #fff; cursor: pointer; line-height: 1; }
.videos-empty { text-align: center; padding: 60px 20px; color: #666; }
```

### 6. Add `renderVideos()` JS function
Groups drills that have a `gdrive_url` by `skill_category`, sorts categories alphabetically, then builds:
- One `.category-row` per category
- A `.video-strip` of `.video-card` elements
- Thumbnail via `https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=${fileId}&sz=w320`
- `onclick="openVideoModal('${d.id}')"` on each card
- If no videos found, show empty-state prompt

```js
function renderVideos() {
  const container = document.getElementById('videosView');
  const withVideo = allDrills.filter(d => getDriveFileId(d.gdrive_url));
  if (withVideo.length === 0) {
    container.innerHTML = '<div class="videos-empty"><h2>No videos uploaded yet</h2>' +
      '<p>Run <code>node run.mjs rugby download</code> to upload videos to Google Drive.</p></div>';
    return;
  }
  // Group by skill_category
  const byCategory = {};
  for (const d of withVideo) {
    const cat = d.skill_category || 'Unclassified';
    if (!byCategory[cat]) byCategory[cat] = [];
    byCategory[cat].push(d);
  }
  const rows = Object.keys(byCategory).sort().map(cat => {
    const cards = byCategory[cat].map(d => {
      const fileId = getDriveFileId(d.gdrive_url);
      const thumbUrl = `https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=${fileId}&sz=w320`;
      const title = escHtml(d.sub_skill || d.canonical_term || d.id);
      const meta = escHtml(d.difficulty || '');
      return `<div class="video-card" onclick="openVideoModal('${d.id}')">` +
        `<img class="video-thumb" src="${thumbUrl}" loading="lazy" onerror="this.style.display='none';this.nextElementSibling.style.display='flex'" alt="${title}">` +
        `<div class="video-thumb-placeholder" style="display:none">&#127945;</div>` +
        `<div class="video-card-info"><div class="video-card-title">${title}</div><div class="video-card-meta">${meta}</div></div>` +
        `</div>`;
    }).join('');
    return `<div class="category-row"><h2>${escHtml(cat)} <span style="color:#555;font-weight:400">(${byCategory[cat].length})</span></h2>` +
      `<div class="video-strip">${cards}</div></div>`;
  }).join('');
  container.innerHTML = `<div class="videos-view">${rows}</div>`;
}
```

### 7. Add `openVideoModal(id)` / `closeVideoModal()` JS functions

```js
function openVideoModal(id) {
  const drill = allDrills.find(d => d.id === id);
  if (!drill) return;
  const fileId = getDriveFileId(drill.gdrive_url);
  if (!fileId) return;
  const embedUrl = `https://drive.google.com/file/d/${fileId}/preview`;
  const title = escHtml(drill.sub_skill || drill.canonical_term || drill.id);
  const cue   = escHtml(drill.coaching_cue || '');
  const backdrop = document.createElement('div');
  backdrop.className = 'video-modal-backdrop';
  backdrop.id = 'videoModal';
  backdrop.innerHTML =
    `<div class="video-modal-inner">` +
    `<iframe class="video-modal-iframe" src="${embedUrl}" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>` +
    `<div class="video-modal-info"><h2>${title}</h2><p>${cue}</p></div>` +
    `</div>` +
    `<button class="video-modal-close" onclick="closeVideoModal()" title="Close">&times;</button>`;
  backdrop.addEventListener('click', e => { if (e.target === backdrop) closeVideoModal(); });
  document.body.appendChild(backdrop);
}

function closeVideoModal() {
  const el = document.getElementById('videoModal');
  if (el) el.remove();
}
// Escape key handler (add once in init)
document.addEventListener('keydown', e => { if (e.key === 'Escape') closeVideoModal(); });
```

### 8. Update `showTab()` to handle `videosView`
Add `document.getElementById('videosView').classList.toggle('hidden', tab !== 'videos')` — or use the `style.display` pattern matching the existing show/hide logic. Also add `renderVideos()` call when switching to `videos` tab if not yet rendered.

### 9. Update `loadData()` to call `renderVideos()` after drills load
Add `renderVideos();` call in the success path of `loadData()`.

---

## Bug fix summary

| Location | Issue | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `toggleCard()` → `fileIdMatch` regex | Only matches `/d/<id>` pattern | Replace with `getDriveFileId()` helper |
| `openVideoModal()` embed URL | Same issue | Uses `getDriveFileId()` from the start |

---

## Verification

1. Run `node run.mjs rugby web` from the vault root
2. Open `http://localhost:5757`
3. Click the **Videos** tab — should show dark Netflix-style layout
4. Confirm category rows appear (Ball Handling, Attack, Defence, etc.)
5. Confirm thumbnails load (may show placeholder on un-shared files)
6. Click a video card — modal should open with embedded Drive player
7. Press Escape or click backdrop — modal should close
8. Return to **Drills** tab and click a card with a video badge — expanded inline video should now work (bug fix validation)

