  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.7); border: none; color: #fff;
  border-radius: 4px; padding: 4px 8px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 0.85rem;
}
.vco-btn:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); }
.vco-delete:hover { background: rgba(220,53,69,0.8); }
```

---

### Phase 6 — Client: Delete function

```js
async function deleteDrill(id) {
  const drill = allDrills.find(d => d.id === id);
  const label = drill ? (drill.sub_skill || drill.id) : id;
  if (!confirm('Remove "' + label + '" from the video library?\n\nThe drill note is kept — only the video link is removed.')) return;
  try {
    const res = await fetch('/api/drills/' + id, { method: 'DELETE' });
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Server error');
    // Remove gdrive_url locally so card disappears
    if (drill) drill.gdrive_url = '';
    renderVideos();
  } catch (e) {
    alert('Failed to remove video: ' + e.message);
  }
}
```

---

### Phase 7 — Client: Edit modal

**`editDrill(id)` function:**
- Finds drill in `allDrills`
- Creates a modal overlay (similar to `openVideoModal`) with a form
- Form fields:
  - Text: sub_skill (Title)
  - Textarea: coaching_cue
  - Select: skill_category (populated from `Object.keys(taxonomy.categories)`)
  - Select: difficulty (beginner / intermediate / advanced)
  - Checkboxes: age_groups (Flag / Mini / Youth / Junior / Senior)
- On submit: `PATCH /api/drills/:id` with changed fields, update `allDrills` in-place, `renderVideos()`, close modal

**Edit modal CSS** (reuses `.video-modal-backdrop` pattern):
```css
